
Paris, 20 May 1780. Gives a sketch of the plan of operations by the French land and naval forces recommended by Mazzei in influential quarters. Has sent a copy of his plan to Rochambeau by the Comte de Deux-Ponts, to whom I gave a letter of recommendation for you dated March 27th. Postscript: John Adams before sailing for America made the first and strong motion towards sending us effectual assistance, and Adams has been warmly seconded in his absence by Lafayette.
